SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: PRIOR TO FILING, THE IRS FORM 990 WILL BE RECEIVED BY THE FINANCE COMMITTEE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: EACH YEAR ALL BOARD MEMBERS AND EMPLOYEES ARE REQUIRED TO COMPLETE A DISCLOSURE STATEMENT. ALSO, ACTIVITIES THAT COULD CAUSE A CONFLICT OF INTEREST ARE MONITORED BY THE ETHICS LIAISON AT THE LOCAL LEVEL AND BY THE ETHICS OMBUDSPERSON AT THE NATIONAL LEVEL.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: BOARD OF DIRECTORS DECIDES EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR COMPENSATION LEVEL, AND IT MUST BE APPROVED BY A MAJORITY OF THE BOD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 18
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: BY SCHEDULING AN APPOINTMENT WITH THE FINANCE DIRECTOR.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: NO GOVERNING DOCUMENTS OR INTERNAL POLICIES ARE AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC. INTERNAL FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ALSO ARE NOT MADE PUBLIC, BUT WE ARE REQUIRED TO FILE AN LM-2 FINANCIAL REPORT WITH THE DEPARTMENT OF LABOR AND THIS DOCUMENT IS PUBLIC VIA THEIR WEBSITE.
